<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_g0ylævzag" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>g˳ylævzag</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kʼwælævzag</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>косноязычный</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>inarticulate</q></cit></sense><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_g0ylævzag." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>ærbakodtoj jæm kʼ˳yrma g˳ylævzagy</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>привели к нему глухого косноязычного</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>there some people brought to him a man who was deaf and could hardly talk</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Марк"/><biblScope>%i7%i 32</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>ærbakodtoj jæm kʼ˳yrma g˳ylævzagy</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>привели к нему глухого косноязычного</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>there some people brought to him a man who was deaf and could hardly talk</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Марк"/><biblScope>%i7%i 32</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Во второй части — <xr><ref target="#entry_ævzag "/></xr> (<xr><ref target="#entry_yvzag"/></xr>) ‘язык’. Первая часть, %ig˳yl%i, не имеет отношения к <xr><ref target="#entry_g0yl"/></xr> ‘пирог’; ее следует сближать с элементом %ikur%i, %ikul%i, %igul%i (см. <xr><ref target="#entry_k0yr-"/></xr>) в названиях телесных недостатков: <xr><ref target="#entry_k0yræfcæg"/></xr> ‘короткошейный’, <xr><ref target="#entry_cænk0yl"/></xr> ‘безрукий’, <xr><ref target="#entry_kʼ0ylyx"/></xr> ‘хромой’, <xr><ref target="#entry_kʼ0yrma"/></xr> ‘глухой’, д. <xr><ref target="#entry_gulu"/></xr> ‘безрогий’ и др. Для д. %ikʼwæl-%i ср. еще д. <xr><ref target="#entry_kʼwælli"/></xr> ‘мозоль’, ‘волдырь’.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">In the second part of the word there is <xr><ref target="#entry_ævzag "/></xr> (<xr><ref target="#entry_yvzag"/></xr>) ‘tongue’. The first part, %ig˳yl%i, is not related to <xr><ref target="#entry_g0yl"/></xr> ‘pie’; it should rather be connected to the element %ikur%i, %ikul%i, %igul%i (see <xr><ref target="#entry_k0yr-"/></xr>) in the infirmity names: <xr><ref target="#entry_k0yræfcæg"/></xr> ‘shortnecked’, <xr><ref target="#entry_cænk0yl"/></xr> ‘armless’, <xr><ref target="#entry_kʼ0ylyx"/></xr> ‘limp’, <xr><ref target="#entry_kʼ0yrma"/></xr> ‘deaf’, Digor <xr><ref target="#entry_gulu"/></xr> ‘hornless’ etc. For Digor %ikʼwæl-%i cf. also Digor <xr><ref target="#entry_kʼwælli"/></xr> ‘callosity’, ‘blister’.</etym></entry>